#

Tuna Pasta Salad

20 min
$10.5
320 kcal
Difficulty: 20%
Servings: 4

Allergens:

FishEggs (in mayonnaise)

Dietary Tags:

High ProteinLow CarbNut-Free

Cuisine:

American

Course:

Main Dish

Tags:

Quick MealSaladCold Dish

Description

A refreshing and protein-packed salad that combines pasta, tuna, and crunchy vegetables, perfect for a quick lunch or dinner.

Ingredients

  • pasta (elbow or rotini): 2 cups
  • canned tuna in water: 1 can (5 oz)
  • cherry tomatoes: 1 cup
  • cucumber: 1 medium
  • sweet corn (canned or frozen): 1 cup
  • mayonnaise: 1/2 cup
  • lemon juice: 2 tablespoons
  • salt: to taste
  • pepper: to taste
  • dried oregano: 1 teaspoon
